s to familiarize test takers with the format of the speak test if you are not able to get online practice test booklets and cd or cassette recordings are available at the aec office register to register for the test come to the aec office located in lippincott hall between a m and p m monday through friday to fill out a request to take the speak test form to be eligible to take the speak test applicants must provide evidence of their general english proficiency applicants may come in any day of the week to fill out a request application they may return any following day a m p m to complete test registration and to set an appointment time this must be done by noon on the day prior to the test guidelines applicants may take the speak test no more than one time every four months refer to the speak test faq page for more information for further details please see the spoken english language competency of faculty and graduate teaching assistants kansas board of regents policy in the ku policy library why ku aec apply founded in as part of a ford foundation campus internationalization grant one of the first intensive english programs in the united states the aec comprises two units the intensive english program iep and short term programs each semester the aec enrolls about students representing more than countries on six continents the applied english center offers field trips and conversation groups to our students learn more ku today upcoming events your browser must support javascript to view this content please enable javascript in your browser settings then try again contact applied english center aec ku edu lippincott hall room jayhawk boulevard lawrence ks aec internal academics admissions alumni athletics campuses giving jobs contact ku lawrence ks maps the university of kansas prohibits discrimination on the basis of race color ethnicity religion sex national origin age ancestry disability status as a veteran sexual orientation marital status parental status gen